 executing the first handler in the queue with these objects as arguments. When processing completes normally, the response is returned.\n\nFor exception handling, any exceptions thrown during handler queue processing are propagated as-is without special handling, though the standard handler configuration typically places GlobalErrorHandler immediately after to catch most errors except fatal ones.\n\n**s3: 設定項目・拡張ポイント**\nGenerating configuration table... Now I'm identifying the cross-references to preserve like NablarchServletContextListener and GlobalErrorHandler, then compiling search hints organized around the WebFrontController class, its handler queue mechanism, request/response flow, and exception handling patterns.\n\nFor the official documentation URLs, since the base URL is empty, I'll end up with just an empty array since there are no Javadoc references to extract either.\n\nGenerating the JSON structure... I'm looking at the configuration details for the handler queue, specifically the GlobalErrorHandler and HttpCharacterEncodingHandler classes that manage error handling and character encoding in the request processing pipeline. 例外が発生した場合は、特別な処理をせずそのまま例外を送出する。標準的なハンドラ構成では直後に GlobalErrorHandler が配置されているため、致命的エラー以外はここで捕捉される。次に、handlerQueue プロパティの構成を確認していて、これはハンドラキューを指定する必須のリスト型プロパティで、標準設定では XML で WebFrontController コンポーネントを定義する際に設定される。","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":21164,"cache_read_input_tokens":29889,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":21164,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7a75f4c8-dfc8-4138-961d-4c0a96850613","uuid":"34fd4cac-4fd7-463b-8502-c9ee2bdf38dd"}
